article.headline: Navy 76, Md.-Eastern Shore 51
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Chris Harris scored 21 points to lead Navy to a 76-51 win over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Tuesday night. Harris scored 18 points during a 32-6 run, which saw the Midshipmen turn a 23-21 deficit into a 53-29 lead with 12:24 left to play. Adam Teague added 14 points, including four 3-pointers, and Kaloe Kina had 11 points for Navy (4-1), which won its fourth straight game after losing its opener. Maryland-Eastern Shore (0-3) was led by Neal Pitt, who scored 18 points, and Keishawn Mayes with 13 points. Pitt was 12 of 15 from the free-throw line. Maryland-Eastern Shore did win the battle of the boards, outrebounding Navy 44-36 with Pitt leading the way with 9.
